abstract: >
  Reproducible analysis scripts for microbial source tracking of centuries-old
  burial soils from the New York African Burial Ground (NYABG). The pipeline
  compares NYABG burial microbiomes (70 burial samples, 6 controls) with Earth
  Microbiome Project (17,482 environmental samples) and Human Microbiome
  Project (4,743 body-site samples) reference cohorts at genus level. Includes
  FEAST source tracking, IndVal indicator species, ANCOM-BC2 and ALDEx2
  differential abundance with cross-method consensus, body-site classification,
  decontamination, and a full sensitivity-and-robustness battery covering
  rarefaction depth, prevalence filter thresholds, body-region confounds,
  pseudoreplication, cranial proximity, soil matrix partitioning, and
  EMP holdout null distributions.
